    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Visual works that constitute deliberate pictures, diagrams, or other marks made directly on the surface of a wall using drawing tools and materials such as ink or graphite rather than paint.These most often dominate the entire surface of the wall. For paintings that are similar in execution, see "mural paintings."</Note_Text>
